cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the dynamic of information spreading in online social networks.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper develops a model to characterize the dynamic patterns of information spreading.
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is another likely category as the paper investigates the impacts of network topology on information spreading in OSNs.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper uses mean-field theory to develop the model.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper tests the model on video sharing data in Renren.
